Difficulty:
Medium
Explanation:
Filtration is necessary to remove low-energy (soft) X-rays that only contribute to patient skin dose without adding to image quality. Regulatory bodies, including the AERB, mandate a minimum total filtration equivalent to 2.5 mm of aluminum for diagnostic X-ray machines operating at 70 kVp or above.
